The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Hotel Leela plans 1:5 stock split

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 Mumbai, June 26: Hotel Leelaventure has decided on a 1:5 stock split and plans to raise between $80 million and $100 million through an overseas flotation to complete its projects in Chennai, Hyderabad, Udaipur and Pune. The share, which carries a face value of Rs 10, will be subdivided into five shares of Rs 2 each.

 It will raise funds either through global depository receipts, foreign currency convertible bonds or equity issue, Hotel Leela informed the BSE today. 

 It has also decided to increase the investment limit for foreign institutional investors to 50 per cent of the paid-up share capital. 

 The board also declared a 5 per cent dividend on non-cumulative redeemable preferrential shares. It also recommended a dividend of 5 per cent on equity shares, aggregating 20 per cent, including interim dividend for the year ended March 31, 2006.




